HLS 251ES-12 ORIGINAL
2025 First Extraordinary Session
HOUSE BILL NO. 4
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAYHAM
ELECTIONS/DATES: Provides for the conduct of fall elections for party primary offices
in 2026 (Item #1)
1 AN ACT
2 To enact Part I-B of Chapter 5 of Title 18 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of 1950, to be
3 comprised of R.S. 18:419, relative to the conduct of fall elections for party primary
4 offices in 2026; to provide for the fall primary election to serve as a primary election
5 for a party primary office to be elected in 2026; to provide for the fall general
6 election to serve as a general election for a party primary office to be elected in
7 2026; to provide for effectiveness; and to provide for related matters.
8 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
9 Section 1. Part I-B of Chapter 5 of Title 18 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes of
10 1950, comprised of R.S. 18:419, is hereby enacted to read as follows:
11 PART I-B. SPECIAL PROVISIONS FOR CERTAIN ELECTIONS HELD IN 2026
12 ยง419. Fall elections in 2026
13 A. Notwithstanding R.S. 18:402(C)(2)(a), the fall primary election held on
14 the first Tuesday after the first Monday in November in 2026 for officers elected at
15 the same time as members of congress in 2026 shall serve as a primary election date
16 for a party primary office to be elected in 2026. A candidate for a party primary
17 office in the primary election shall be elected as provided in R.S. 18:511.
18 B. Notwithstanding R.S. 18:402(C)(2)(b), the fall general election held on
19 the sixth Saturday after the first Tuesday after the first Monday in November of 2026
20 shall serve as a general election date for a party primary office to be elected in 2026.
